  <!-- Covered Call Strategy Explanation -->
  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>Understanding JEPQ's Nasdaq Covered Call Strategy</h2>
    <p>JEPQ's sophisticated approach to income generation combines equity ownership with option strategies to maximize income while maintaining growth exposure.</p>

    <div class="strategy-explanation">
      <div class="strategy-step">
        <h4>Step 1: Nasdaq 100 Stock Selection</h4>
        <p>JEPQ holds a diversified portfolio of Nasdaq 100 stocks, focusing on large-cap technology companies like Apple, Microsoft, Amazon, and Google. This provides exposure to high-growth potential while collecting corporate dividends.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-step">
        <h4>Step 2: Covered Call Writing</h4>
        <p>The fund systematically sells call options on its equity positions. These calls are typically out-of-the-money, allowing for some upside participation while generating substantial premium income from the high implied volatility of tech stocks.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-step">
        <h4>Step 3: Premium Collection</h4>
        <p>Option premiums are collected monthly and distributed to shareholders along with dividend income from the underlying stocks. Higher market volatility increases option premiums, boosting distribution amounts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-step">
        <h4>Step 4: Risk Management</h4>
        <p>JPMorgan's active management team adjusts strike prices and expiration dates based on market conditions, volatility levels, and technical analysis to optimize the risk/reward profile of the covered call overlay.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="strategy-benefits">
      <h4>Key Benefits of the Strategy:</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Enhanced Income:</strong> Generates 4-6% additional yield beyond stock dividends alone</li>
        <li><strong>Downside Buffer:</strong> Option premiums provide cushion during market declines</li>
        <li><strong>Monthly Cash Flow:</strong> Consistent income regardless of market direction</li>
        <li><strong>Active Management:</strong> Professional optimization of option strikes and timing</li>
        <li><strong>Growth Participation:</strong> Maintains upside exposure up to call strike prices</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="strategy-risks">
      <h4>Potential Limitations:</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Capped Upside:</strong> Strong bull markets may see limited participation</li>
        <li><strong>Tax Implications:</strong> Option income taxed as ordinary income</li>
        <li><strong>Complexity:</strong> More sophisticated than traditional dividend ETFs</li>
        <li><strong>Volatility Dependency:</strong> Lower volatility reduces option premium income</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

